  <li id="comment-18787" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://backtothecuttingboard.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Emily</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2009/12/for-ever-and-ever/#comment-18787"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-12-13T20:26:54-05:00">Sunday, December 13, 2009 at 8:26 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I found almost this exact recipe on another food blog a few weeks ago and have been unable to stop making it.  It&#39;s so addictive!  </p>
<p>And what makes it even better is that you can make the caramel in the microwave, which makes it even faster and you don&#39;t have to bother with candy thermometers.  I&#39;ve made it at least 6 or 8 times and it&#39;s been perfect every time.  </p>
<p>You just microwave the sugar, corn syrup and butter for 30 seconds and stir well.  Then put it back in for 2 minutes. It will be bubbling when you take it out, so quickly and carefully stir in the baking soda and vanilla. Then pour it over the popcorn and bake, like you said.  </p>
<p>The baking is definitely what makes the caramel corn good.  I usually only bake it for 15-20 minutes because I can&#39;t wait much longer than that. üôÇ</p>
    </div>

