    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;m evangelical about do-it-yourself microwave popcorn a la Alton Brown.  Put 1/4 &#8211; 1/3 cup popcorn in a brown paper lunch bag, fold the top over twice, and close with two (no more, no less) staples.  It cooks in a little over two minutes in my microwave.  I usually swirl it in a bowl with some olive oil and garlic Tabasco and sprinkle with yeast flakes, but caramel may be in order.</p>
