  <li id="comment-18865" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Sheila</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2009/12/for-ever-and-ever/#comment-18865"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-12-17T12:45:21-05:00">Thursday, December 17, 2009 at 12:45 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>If making big batches to be used for gifts, why not pop the corn in a covered pan on the stovetop?  Save a lot of $$$ and could not be easier.  Stove, pan, oil (not olive), popcorn, lid, med. high heat &#8211; nothing to it.  Also, popcorn can be popped in the microwave in a brown paper lunch-size bag.  with or without oil. just cover the bottom end of the bag with a layer of popcorn, add a little oil (if you desire), fold down top an inch or two, lay bag on its side on a microwavable plate and microwave for about 2 min or so. Basic, basic food.</p>
    </div>

