    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Second time I made this, I doubled it but forgot to double the butter, and it came out fine. I also added a healthy dash of cinnamon, and it was killer! First time I did a double batch as well, in the microwave (almost harder b/c if you let it go too long it can pour all over your microwave). Made one batch regular, and the other I threw coconut and almonds in with the popcorn, poured the caramel over, then tossed it. Also, I baked it in roasting pans every time &#8212; easier to stir. <br />But, use your imagination, and your pantry contents, to change up the flavors! The cinnamon was my fav.</p>
    </div>

