      <p>I&#39;m confused about the temperature of the sugar. When you cook sugar, it goes through different stages based on its temperature, and 250 degrees is the hard crack stage &#8211; it isn&#39;t even near the caramel stage, which is around 350 degrees. At 250 degrees, the sugar is still clear. I&#39;m going to make this and check it out. It sounds good.</p>
